in the command line, type:

sudo apt-get install python-imaging-tk
sudo apt-get install qt4-dev-tools
sudo apt-get install python-qt4
pip install pyqtgraph


Then, go into the raspberry pi's configuration settings by typing

sudo raspi-config
-Navigate to option 5 Interfacing Options
-Navigate to P4 SPI
-Select yes to enable SPI

Move the noulsmatic_startup.sh file to the Desktop and type into the terminal
sudo chmod +x noulsmatic_startup.sh

Alternatively, move the text file "Ventilator Software" to the Desktop, where it should become a launcher

If you do this, make noulsmatic_startup.sh executable by navigating to the noulsmatic folder in the terminal and typing the chmod line

*****To get respiratory monitoring to work right*****
There's a file that, when it runs causes something to be set correctly in the pi and read the pressure transducer correctly. This needs a few modules

Type into the terminal:
pip3 install adafruit-circuitpython-mcp3xxx
